East 134th Street, north side, east from Brook to St. Anns Aves., sshowing part of the area which was cleared for the construction of an approach to the Triborough Bridge by the demolition of numerous buildings. The buildings in the background are on the north side of East 135th Street.
July 29, 1937.
P. L. Sperr.

Brook Ave., west side, north from Southern Boulevard to East 135th Street and showing a gas station at the N.W. corner of the Boulevard. Factory buildings, shown face on the south side of East 134th Street, between Brook and Brown Aves.

May 11, 1937.

P. L. Sperr.

(1)
Brook Ave., north from but not including Southern Boulevard.
Note demolition of entire block of 4-story buildings on the east side of the avenue from East 134th to East 135th Streets.

P. L. Sperr.

(2)
A closer view of the demolished block of houses which bore the Nos. 128 to 142.

P. L. Sperr.
